frameDefinitions: An Agent acts so as to cause some process to begin again after an interruption or suspension.
An Entity comes into existence at a particular Place and Time which may take a certain Duration_of_endstate, have a Cause, or be formed from Components.
A Recipient starts off without the Theme in their possession, and then comes to possess it.
An Entity ends up with some Final_quality--a new fact about the Entity.
Despite some implication that a State would be interrupted, the Entity remains in the specified State.
An Entity ends up in a Final_category, Final_situation, or Final_quality which it was not in before.
frameExamples: The two countries <t>revived</t> diplomatic relations after a lull of five years.
Problems may <t>arise</t> whenever an S1 sophont enters the game.
listRoleDefinitions: A sentient being acts with the intention of causing a process to begin again.
The process which begins again after a suspension.
The period of time during which the process is suspended.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that causes the process to resume. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of Causes.
The time at which the process is restarted.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> causes the <fen>Process</fen> to resume.
Concrete or abstract entity that did not exist before the <fen>Time</fen> of the event.
This role identifes the Time when a new Entity comes into existence.
This is the Place where the new Entity comes into being.
The <fen>Recipient</fen> indicates the entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes possession.
When the event occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> denotes where the Getting takes place.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change, newly ending up in the <fen>Final_category</fen> or taking on a new <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
>When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.
A concrete or abstract <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>State</fen> is found to still persist.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the <fen>State</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which undergoes a change, ending up in the <fen>Final_category</fen>, <fen>Final_situation</fen>, or <fen>Final_quality</fen>.
When the change occurs.
Where the change takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The driver</fex> restarted the truck after it stalled.
The two countries revived diplomatic relations <fex>after a lull of five years</fex>.
<fex>The spring rains</fex> restarted the flow of the stream.
This state reinstated the death penalty <fex>in 1975</fex>.
The two nations revived relations <fex>in Geneva</fex> during the latest round of talks.
<fex>By 1945</fex> he had become uncertain of the advisability of anyone having such a weapon.
Martial law remains in effect <fex>in Absurdistan</fex>.
